kagome — Japanese morphological analyzer
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Files:    internal/kagome/ (entire subtree)
Source:   https://github.com/ikawaha/kagome (v2)
          https://github.com/ikawaha/kagome-dict
License:  MIT

Source files from kagome and kagome-dict are vendored under internal/kagome
with import paths rewritten to point inside this module. The bundled
ipa.dict is the IPA dictionary derived from mecab-ipadic-2.7.0-20070801
(NAIST / ICOT Free Software terms). See internal/kagome/NOTICE for the
detailed attribution and full upstream license text.

The Japanese transliterator at languages/jpan uses kagome to obtain a
kana reading for kanji-bearing tokens before running the existing Hepburn
mapper over the reading.

